Please STOP measuring your effectiveness 
Without your consistency in practice.

Microblading is a skill that will only be developed by PRACTICE, there is no talent needed here. I PROMISE! 

When I was a student I felt I was not made for this! If you know my story... you know I borrowed the money to take my first microblading course and no matter what I had to pay back.

So no matter how my feelings were during my practice I decided to put priority and set a time for some latex practice! 

Some students  ask me if “I think they will be good at microblading?”and my answer is “I can’t judge your success or failure without at least 2-3 months of consistent practice!”

Some student want to track their success without little record of practice. Practicing for at least 30 min to 1 hour a day will set you up for success.

And is ok to feel overwhelmed and step away for 1 day, it happened to me all the time. Just make sure to come back😅 

This is like preparing your self for a 
marathon! It will be worth it, but we all have to go through the pains of being a successful microblading artist! 

It has been life changing for me and now I get to witness how life changing it is for my students! 

Leslie from 2023 wants to thank Leslie from 2016 of NOT GIVING UP! I am sure you will thank yourself later too! 

You got this BROWBOSS💕

It is crucial to ask for a deposit as a microblading artist for several reasons: 

✅ Commitment: Requesting a deposit helps ensure that clients are committed to their appointment. It acts as a form of confirmation that they intend to show up for the scheduled session. Without a deposit, there is a higher risk of last-minute cancellations or no-shows, which can result in lost time and income for the artist.

✅ Reservation of Time and Resources: Microblading is a meticulous and time-consuming procedure. By asking for a deposit, you can reserve a specific time slot for the client, blocking out other potential appointments during that period. It allows you to manage your schedule effectively and allocate the necessary time and resources for each client.

✅ Financial Security: Microblading requires the use of specialized equipment, pigments, and other supplies. Collecting a deposit helps cover some of these costs upfront and provides financial security for the artist.

✅ Professionalism and Trust: Requesting a deposit demonstrates professionalism and establishes trust between the artist and the client. 

✅ Filtering Serious Inquiries: Asking for a deposit can help filter out clients who are not genuinely interested in getting microblading done. 

It’s important to establish clear policies and communicate them effectively to your clients. Be transparent about your deposit requirements, including the amount, refund policy, and any other relevant details. This helps manage expectations and ensures a smooth and professional client experience.

From chasing profits to creating impact. My journey with microblading has evolved, and now it’s all about making a difference. Boosting confidence, restoring normalcy, and enhancing natural beauty.

Shifting your mindset towards creating a positive impact can bring a deeper sense of fulfillment and purpose to your work. 

Here are a few reasons why making a difference through microblading is valuable:

✅ Boosting Confidence and Self-esteem: Microblading can help individuals who have lost their eyebrows due to various reasons, such as medical conditions or treatments, regain their confidence and self-esteem.

✅ Restoring a Sense of Normalcy: For people who have experienced hair loss due to conditions like alopecia or accidents, microblading can provide a sense of normalcy and improve their quality of life.

✅ Enhancing Natural Beauty: Microblading is an art that can be used to enhance the natural features of individuals. By skillfully shaping and filling in eyebrows, you can bring out their unique beauty and contribute to their self-expression.

✅ Empowering Others: As a microblading artist, you have the opportunity to empower others by sharing your knowledge and skills.

✅ Building Relationships and Trust: Through your work, you can establish meaningful connections with your clients. By listening to their needs, providing a comfortable experience, and delivering high-quality results, you build trust and rapport.

Each stroke carries the power to empower and uplift. It’s more than just art; it’s about changing lives. 

Join me on this transformative path, where every brow tells a story of self-love and empowerment. #microbladingwithpurpose #makingadifference

Ever wondered why microblading comes with a higher price tag? Let me break it down for you:

📚 Extensive Training: Our artists undergo rigorous training and certification to master the art of microblading, ensuring they deliver exceptional results.

🛡️ Insurance Coverage: Your safety is our top priority. We invest in professional liability insurance to protect both you and our artists in case of any unforeseen complications.

💆‍♀️ Health and Well-being: We prioritize the well-being of our artists by visiting chiropractors regularly, maintaining proper body alignment for steady hands and optimal performance.

👀 Eye Care Matters: Regular visits to ophthalmologists ensure our artists maintain excellent vision, enabling them to create precise, stunning brows.

💎 Quality Materials: We spare no expense when it comes to using top-notch, sterile disposable needles, high-quality pigments, and other supplies, ensuring your safety and satisfaction.

⏱️ Time and Attention: Microblading is an art that demands meticulous attention to detail. Our artists take the time to create beautifully natural-looking brows, tailored specifically to you.

💼 Exceptional Customer Service: We believe in providing you with the best experience from start to finish. Our dedicated receptionist ensures excellent customer service, handling appointments and addressing any inquiries or concerns.

💪 Respecting Costs, Respecting Results: By respecting our prices, we can maintain the highest standards and deliver outstanding, long-lasting results you'll love.

Choose expertise and experience over price alone – you deserve the best. Unlock your beauty potential with our premium microblading services today! ✨

✨True Representation: Fresh microblading can appear crisp, dark, and very defined. However, it’s the healed results that show how the strokes and pigment will genuinely look once settled into the skin.

✨Pigment Retention: Evaluating healed photos lets you see how well the artist’s techniques and chosen pigments retain in the skin.

✨Color Consistency: Healed results offer insight into whether the artist can choose pigments that heal true to color, without undesirable undertones like blue or pink emerging over time.

✨Tailored Techniques: Everyone’s skin is different, and a one-size-fits-all approach doesn’t work in microblading. Healed results can show if the artist tailors their technique to different skin types and challenges. 

✨Transparency and Honesty: An artist willing to show healed results is likely more transparent and honest about their work, which is a positive indicator of their professionalism and confidence in their skills.

✨ Optimal Depth on First Pass: 
The initial microblading stroke, or the “first pass” must be at the perfect depth - not too deep, not too shallow. I call this the “sweet spot”. Achieving this depth is crucial as it lays the foundation for how the brows will heal. Using a three-way stretching technique helps hit this depth accurately, ensuring the strokes blend naturally with the existing brows. 

✨Effective Masking and Numbing: 
After the first pass, immediately mask the brows with pigment and apply numbing gel with ephinephrine (ephi). This step is crucial for two reasons: it minimizes bleeding, and it helps the pigment settle properly into the stroke lines. This careful application ensures that the pigment stays put and heals in a way that looks natural and consistent. 

✨Limited Passes and Final Masking: 
To prevent overworking the skin, I limit myself to only two passes per stroke, if needed. After the second pass, the area is masked again for 5-7 minutes, followed by another application of numbing gel before removing the pigment mask. This limited intervention approach reduces skin trauma, promoting a more natural healing process and final appearance.

These three key practices, the likelihood of achieving natural-looking, well-healed microblading results is significantly increased. Each step is designed to reduce trauma to the skin, ensuring the brows heal in a way that mimics natural brows as closely as possible.
